					<div class="commentheading">On September 30, 2009 at 01:18 PM, alex (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>Making mixing easier</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">If you have  a Kitchen Aid, the following should help you out:<br />
<br />
For creaming the butter and sugar together, use the paddle as the directions above suggest.<br />
<br />
When it's time to add the flour mixture, change to the dough hook and put the shields on.  Turn the mixer on the lowest setting or one notch up from this.  Use a large metal spoon and spoon in the flour mixture one spoon at a time.  This will keep the flour from getting all over the sides of the bowl. <br />
<br />
Because of the shape of the dough hook, you can also add in the chocolate chips instead of mixing by hand - it won't smash them up like the paddle can.</div>
